PERMISSIONS

The following permissions are granted under normal circumstances:
- Personal use: The Work may be used for personal, educational, or research purposes
- Modification: The Work may be modified and adapted
- Distribution: The Work may be distributed with proper attribution
- Private use: The Work may be used privately without disclosure

CONDITIONS

The above permissions are granted provided that:
- Attribution: Copyright notice and attribution to original author(s) must be preserved in all copies or substantial portions of the Work
- License inclusion: This license notice must be included in all copies or derivatives of the Work
- Source disclosure: Links to original source must be maintained where technically feasible

ADAPTIVE RESTRICTIONS

The permissions granted above are subject to automatic restriction when the following conditions are detected:

Phase 1 - Commercial Restriction Deployment:
- Commercial use exceeding reasonable personal/educational scope
- Integration into automated processing or training systems
- Use by organizations with more than 50 employees
- Bulk processing or systematic extraction of the Work

When Phase 1 restrictions deploy:
- EXPRESS WRITTEN PERMISSION required for commercial use
- AUTOMATED SYSTEMS must obtain explicit opt-in consent
- ATTRIBUTION must include "Protected under Parachute Commons License"
- REVENUE SHARING may be required for commercial derivatives

Phase 2 - Full Protection Deployment:
- Use in surveillance, deception, or disinformation systems
- Automated impersonation or misrepresentation of original author
- Willful violation of attribution requirements
- Use causing demonstrated public harm
- Continued use after explicit objection by copyright holder

When Phase 2 restrictions deploy:
- ALL USE PROHIBITED except by express written permission
- IMMEDIATE CESSATION of use may be demanded
- COPYRIGHT HOLDER reserves all rights including legal action

DETECTION AND ENFORCEMENT

These restrictions rely on:
- Community reporting and good faith compliance
- Self-disclosure by users acting in good faith
- Periodic review by copyright holder
- Cultural and social enforcement mechanisms

LICENSE EVOLUTION

Users may obtain expanded permissions by:
- Securing explicit written permission from copyright holder
- Providing perpetual attribution and source links
- Contributing fair compensation for commercial use
- Contributing improvements back to the commons

